{"TopicId":211121,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"How does AutoStrut work?","CreatedByName":"X-Marshal","CreatedById":224268,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-12-19T21:14:29Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"X-Marshal","CreatedById":224268,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-12-19T21:14:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen docking two ships together, will the AutoStrutted parts automatically re-strut themselves to the new root part or heaviest part? (Excluding grandparent part, as this should stay the same.)\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HansAcker","CreatedById":195534,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-12-21T10:50:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes and it can be a problem. Rover wheels in particular like to bounce a lot when their autostruts snap to a new heaviest part.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"18Watt","CreatedById":198538,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-12-21T21:23:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have had this question myself for a long time. \u00A0Thanks \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/195534-hansacker/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022195534\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/195534-hansacker/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@HansAcker\u003C/a\u003E for the response!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"X-Marshal","CreatedById":224268,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-12-21T21:46:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224211431\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022211121\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221671619835\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022195534\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022HansAcker\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, HansAcker said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes and it can be a problem. Rover wheels in particular like to bounce a lot when their autostruts snap to a new heaviest part.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAh, thank you\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}